data.title: 117 Chapter 3
data.meta_description: 117 Chapter 3 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Radio navigational warnings are broadcasts that provide maritime safety information to aid navigation. They include worldwide, long-range, and coastal/local warnings. Coastal warnings cover specific ports and harbors, while long-range warnings assist ships at sea. The United States participates in worldwide coordination of these broadcasts through various agencies and systems.
